1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to schools; to require display of the state
2 motto and the national motto; and to authorize contributions.
3 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB122 LB122
2025 2025
1 Section 1. (1) On and after the effective date of this act, each
2 school board shall prominently display the national motto of the United
3 States, "In God We Trust", and the state motto of Nebraska, "Equality
4 Under the Law", written legibly in English on a poster or plaque no less
5 than eight and one-half by eleven inches in size, in each classroom or in
6 another prominent place in each school building where each student is
7 able to see and read it each day school is in session.
8 (2) A school board may accept contributions to defray the costs of
9 implementing this section.
